FIGURE SKATING - STOJKO LEADS AFTER SHORT PROGRAM . Former two - time world champion Elvis Stojko of Canada led the men at Skate Canada International after the short programme Thursday . Ilia Kulik of Russia was second and Michael Weiss of the United States was third in the short programme , which counts for one - third of the total score . The other two - thirds will be determined in Saturday ' s free skate . In the pairs short programme , defending world champions Marina Eltsova and Andrei Bushkov of Russia were first , Americans Kyoko Ina and Jason Dungjen second , and Germans Mandy Woetzel and Ingo Steuer third . Skate Canada is the second major international event of the figure skating season . 
